# Information Security Management – Welcome Challenge

This repository documents my work on the *Welcome Challenge* from the WS23 Information Security Management course at the University of Vienna.

## Overview

The challenge involved connecting to a remote service via TCP and exploring its behavior to understand how it operates.

## Skills & Concepts

* TCP communication (using tools like netcat)
* Remote service interaction
* Basic security challenge methodology
* Understanding flag-based systems

## Notes

Due to academic integrity policies, challenge solutions, flags, and sensitive details are not included.

